entire: nor height nor depth, nor any other created thing, shall be able to separate us from the love of God which is in Christ Jesus our Lord.

Love suffers long and is kind; love does not envy; love does not parade itself, is not puffed up; does not behave rudely, does not seek its own, is not provoked, thinks no evil; does not rejoice in iniquity, but rejoices in the truth;

fragment: Let all that you do be done with love
entire: Let all that you do be done with love.

fragment: walk by faith / not by sight
entire: For we walk by faith, not by sight.

fragment: I have been crucified with Christ
entire: I have been crucified with Christ; it is no longer I who live, but Christ lives in me; and the life which I now live in the flesh I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me and gave Himself for me.

fragment: For by grace you have been saved through faith
entire: For by grace you have been saved through faith, and that not of yourselves; it is the gift of God, not of works, lest anyone should boast.

fragment: I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me
entire: I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me.

fragment: for God has not given us a spirit of fear
entire: For God has not given us a spirit of fear, but of power and of love and of a sound mind.

fragment: faith is the substance of things hoped for
entire: Now faith is the substance of things hoped for, the evidence of things not seen.

fragment: My brethren, count it all joy when you fall into various trials
entire: My brethren, count it all joy when you fall into various trials, knowing that the testing of your faith produces patience. But let patience have its perfect work, that you may be perfect and complete, lacking nothing.

fragment: casting all your care upon Him, for He cares for you
entire: casting all your care upon Him, for He cares for you.

fragment: There is no fear in love but perfect love casts out fear
entire: There is no fear in love; but perfect love casts out fear, because fear involves torment. But he who fears has not been made perfect in love.

fragment: And God will wipe away every tear from their eyes
entire: And God will wipe away every tear from their eyes; there shall be no more death, nor sorrow, nor crying. There shall be no more pain, for the former things have passed away.

I would have lost heart, unless I had believed
That I would see the goodness of the LORD
In the land of the living.

Where there is no revelation, the people cast off restraint;
But happy is he who keeps the law.

fragment: she laughs at time to come
entire:
Strength and honor are her clothing;
She laughs at the time to come.
Now may He who supplies seed to the sower, and bread for food, supply and multiply the seed you have sown and increase the fruits of your righteousness,
Now all things are of God, who has reconciled us to Himself through Jesus Christ, and has given us the ministry of reconciliation,

Let the redeemed of the LORD say so,
Whom He has redeemed from the hand of the enemy,
Therefore I say to you, do not worry about your life, what you will eat or what you will drink; nor about your body, what you will put on. Is not life more than food and the body more than clothing?
Now He did not do many mighty works there because of their unbelief.

Some trust in chariots, and some in horses;
But we will remember the name of the LORD our God.
Speak to all the congregation of the children of Israel, and say to them: ‘You shall be holy, for I the LORD your God am holy.
And the vessel that he made of clay was marred in the hand of the potter; so he made it again into another vessel, as it seemed good to the potter to make.
He who loves his life will lose it, and he who hates his life in this world will keep it for eternal life.

He then said, “God’s word: Dig ditches all over this valley. Here’s what will happen—you won’t hear the wind, you won’t see the rain, but this valley is going to fill up with water and your army and your animals will drink their fill. This is easy for God to do; he will also hand over Moab to you. You will ravage the country: Knock out its fortifications, level the key villages, clear-cut the orchards, clog the springs, and litter the cultivated fields with stones.” In the morning—it was at the hour of morning sacrifice—the water had arrived, water pouring in from the west, from Edom, a flash flood filling the valley with water.

Your eyes will see the King in His beauty;
They will see the land that is very far off.

fragment: hands for war / bow of bronze
entire: He teaches my hands to war so that my arms can bend a bow of bronze.
